Project Overview
This project is a simple console-based attendance tracking system developed using Python.
It allows the user to record whether each student is present or absent and generates an attendance summary including totals and percentage.

Features
Record attendance for multiple students
Mark students as Present or Absent
Store data using dictionary
Calculate total present and absent
Compute attendance percentage
Display attendance summary

Problem Statement
To design and implement an attendance tracking system that allows the user to mark students as present or absent and display a summary including total present, total absent, and attendance percentage.

Objective
To track student attendance using Python
To use loops and conditional statements
To apply dictionary data structure
To calculate attendance percentage
To understand basic logic building

Tools Used
Python 3
VS Code / IDLE

Description
This project simulates a simple attendance tracking system.
The user inputs the number of students and records attendance as Present or Absent for each student.
The data is stored using a dictionary, and the system calculates totals and percentage based on the input.

Algorithm
Start the program
Read number of students
Create an empty dictionary for attendance
Loop through each student
Read attendance input (P/A)
If input is P → mark Present
Else → mark Absent
Count total Present and Absent
Calculate attendance percentage
Display summary
Stop the program

Conclusion
This project demonstrates how Python can be used to build a simple attendance tracking system using loops, conditional statements, and dictionary data structures to manage and process student data efficiently.
